Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 41 points to spoil Paolo Banchero's return to the Magic's lineup
Post-Match Reflections: Paolo Banchero said he had a chip on his shoulder now and might have to make up for lost time.
Magic coach Jamahl Mosley said Paolo Banchero's performance was a testament to his work ethic and poise.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Paolo Banchero returned to the Magic's lineup after a 34-game absence due to an oblique injury.
The Magic fell to the Milwaukee Bucks 109-106 in Paolo Banchero's first game back.
Others: Paolo Banchero was 11-for-21 from the field, plus added seven rebounds, three assists and three steals in 27 minutes.
The Magic entered Friday in the No. 4 spot in the Eastern Conference and lost their first four without Banchero, then went 19-11 during the remainder of his absence.
